WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.141
Open the Command Center.

p02
00:00:01.141 --> 00:00:05.224
This is your first look when a site calls in a dead register.

p03
00:00:05.224 --> 00:00:08.162
The dashboard pulls the whole network into one view,

p04
00:00:08.162 --> 00:00:11.300
and the panel you want is lower down, under the map.

p05
00:00:11.841 --> 00:00:13.639
Find Priority Intelligence.

p06
00:00:13.978 --> 00:00:16.933
It ranks what needs you right now, worst first.

p07
00:00:17.205 --> 00:00:19.739
Eleven items today, four of them urgent,

p08
00:00:19.972 --> 00:00:22.640
and the Critical group is already sitting at the top.

p09
00:00:23.064 --> 00:00:23.834
There it is.

p10
00:00:24.229 --> 00:00:29.060
Henrico West Broad, POS system offline, card terminals down at peak.

p11
00:00:29.609 --> 00:00:33.666
The row names the site, the symptom, and tells you a tech is already en route.

p12
00:00:33.981 --> 00:00:36.400
Check one is done before you lifted a finger.

p13
00:00:36.936 --> 00:00:37.936
Now look right,

p14
00:00:38.140 --> 00:00:38.937
not through.

p15
00:00:39.367 --> 00:00:41.702
The row has an Open arrow into the item.

p16
00:00:41.910 --> 00:00:46.133
We leave it alone on the shared demo, and this pass did not capture where it lands.

p17
00:00:46.729 --> 00:00:49.688
What earns your attention is Action Ownership beside it:

p18
00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:53.848
Regional Ops already holds this one, due inside thirty minutes.

p19
00:00:54.165 --> 00:00:56.000
Know who owns it before you move.

p20
00:00:56.451 --> 00:01:00.124
Head to I-T and Support, and open M-L Command Center.

p21
00:01:00.482 --> 00:01:05.772
This is the Micrologic N-O-C, the room support watches across every customer.

p22
00:01:06.150 --> 00:01:09.667
Two criticals live right now, and the incidents tab is where they land.

p23
00:01:10.205 --> 00:01:11.570
Read the top incident.

p24
00:01:12.365 --> 00:01:16.991
POS system offline, zero transactions for forty-seven minutes.

p25
00:01:17.387 --> 00:01:18.906
That zero is the tell.

p26
00:01:19.423 --> 00:01:23.022
A slow lane still writes tickets;

p27
00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:25.600
a stopped one does not, and this one stopped almost an hour ago.

p28
00:01:26.046 --> 00:01:28.038
Two things on that card do your triage.

p29
00:01:28.615 --> 00:01:30.086
The tag tells you what broke:

p30
00:01:30.622 --> 00:01:32.252
this one reads Tunnel Down,

p31
00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:35.446
others say Hardware, Payments, Equipment.

p32
00:01:36.411 --> 00:01:38.266
The assignee tells you who has it,

p33
00:01:38.735 --> 00:01:41.235
or that it is unassigned and yours to claim.

p34
00:01:42.186 --> 00:01:47.502
Create Ticket and View Full Profile are right there, but on the demo you only read them.

p35
00:01:47.952 --> 00:01:51.275
Next check is System Alerts, under I-T and Support.

p36
00:01:52.103 --> 00:01:57.047
Open it from the sidebar link and the live feed loads, three active alerts, one critical.

p37
00:01:57.721 --> 00:02:02.126
Every row names its type, tunnel, P-O-S, chemical, network,

p38
00:02:02.406 --> 00:02:04.531
and today's P-O-S row is a warning,

p39
00:02:04.801 --> 00:02:07.925
low receipt paper on P-O-S two, still active.

p40
00:02:08.657 --> 00:02:11.134
Filter to the site and read what is still open there.

p41
00:02:11.793 --> 00:02:14.488
Into Settings, Hardware, Terminals.

p42
00:02:15.105 --> 00:02:17.857
This is the register you would check for that offline complaint.

p43
00:02:18.339 --> 00:02:20.864
There is a plus New Record button up top; leave it alone.

p44
00:02:21.179 --> 00:02:25.105
We are here to read, not to register anything.

p45
00:02:25.564 --> 00:02:27.292
Run your eye across the columns.

p46
00:02:27.754 --> 00:02:28.272
Terminal,

p47
00:02:28.555 --> 00:02:29.314
location,

p48
00:02:29.673 --> 00:02:30.328
I-P,

p49
00:02:30.601 --> 00:02:31.653
software version,

p50
00:02:31.898 --> 00:02:32.565
O-S,

p51
00:02:32.836 --> 00:02:33.782
and Last Seen.

p52
00:02:34.439 --> 00:02:37.867
Over a thousand terminals load here, and notice what is missing:

p53
00:02:38.159 --> 00:02:40.189
no active or status column.

p54
00:02:40.527 --> 00:02:44.930
So Last Seen is your answer, the moment each register last checked in.

p55
00:02:45.316 --> 00:02:49.148
Search the site, find the terminal, and read how long it has been quiet.

p56
00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:52.512
Last surface: Sales, then Tickets.

p57
00:02:53.031 --> 00:02:54.863
This is the live pulse of the lane.

p58
00:02:55.328 --> 00:02:56.714
The list carries Location, Ticket number,

p59
00:02:57.020 --> 00:02:58.835
Date and Time, Total,

p60
00:02:59.142 --> 00:03:03.857
Status, Tender Type, and Customer, with a running total up top.

p61
00:03:04.395 --> 00:03:07.290
Filter to the site, then read the newest time stamp.

p62
00:03:07.910 --> 00:03:11.214
If the last ticket is minutes old, the lane is still writing.

p63
00:03:11.769 --> 00:03:16.535
If it has been quiet for a stretch, that matches the N-O-C's zero transactions,

p64
00:03:16.885 --> 00:03:19.267
and now you have a hard outage in writing.

p65
00:03:19.553 --> 00:03:20.498
Skip Export.

p66
00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:22.059
Now escalate,

p67
00:03:22.426 --> 00:03:23.004
cleanly.

p68
00:03:23.803 --> 00:03:26.691
Open Support Tickets and raise one with four things:

p69
00:03:27.053 --> 00:03:29.491
the location code, the terminal I-D,

p70
00:03:29.752 --> 00:03:32.450
the last-ticket time, and any alert I-Ds.

p71
00:03:33.264 --> 00:03:38.311
The queue sorts by Ticket, Category, Location, Owner, Age, and Priority.

p72
00:03:38.886 --> 00:03:40.715
Migration switches are the exception;

p73
00:03:41.013 --> 00:03:42.786
those go to Jira, not here.

p74
00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:45.194
That is the whole loop.

p75
00:03:45.194 --> 00:03:47.912
Priority Intelligence to confirm the flag and its owner.

p76
00:03:47.912 --> 00:03:51.522
The N-O-C for what broke and who has it.

p77
00:03:51.522 --> 00:03:53.938
System Alerts and Terminals for the hardware picture.

p78
00:03:53.938 --> 00:03:58.547
And the ticket feed to show whether the lane is still writing.

p79
00:03:58.547 --> 00:04:00.661
Run them in that order every time,

p80
00:04:00.661 --> 00:04:05.794
and your escalation carries the four facts a field tech needs to move without calling you back.

